      "writtenOn": "2017-12-14T22:00:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You’ve basically got to duplicate this visibility hack in zlib and other targets that we only want to pick up from the dependencies file too, right? And mini_chromium’s base…that one’s tricky, because it’s in a different repository.\n\nI dunno, do you still think that it’s better to have that knowledge in a central dependencies file when we still need to pollute all of these targets that need special crashpad_in_chromium handling with other stuff? Or should we just decentralize the crashpad_in_chromium handling to the edges?",
      "revId": "9b02561e15936328f1c9e02bad4545cdd69a5bbd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
